              concentrations. Altogether, our results show that acclimation to temperature and CO 
              2 
              is primarily related to resource conservation at the leaf level. Under future, warmer, high CO 
              2 
              conditions, plants are therefore likely to use less nutrients for leaf‐level photosynthesis, which may impact whole‐plant to ecosystem functioning.},
